Johannesburg - World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) will head to South Africa next year with several wrestling stars to make an appearance. Tickets for WWE LIVE SOUTH AFRICA will go on sale on Wednesday, December 13 from 09:00, with fans able to buy tickets from bigconcerts.co.za and computicket.com.There will be three WWE events hosted in Cape Town, Johannesburg and Pretoria.    The WWE LIVE SOUTH AFRICA tour begins at the Grand Arena, GrandWest in Cape Town on Wednesday, April 18, before debuting at the Sun Arena, Time Square in Pretoria on Friday, April 20.   The tour concludes at the Ticketpro Dome in Johannesburg on Saturday, April 21.   The family-friendly events will feature WWE superstars Braun Strowman , Seth Rollins , Dean Ambrose , Intercontinental Champion Roman Reigns , RAW Women’s champion Alexa Bliss , Sasha Banks , Asuka , RAW Tag Team champions Cesaro and Sheamus , to name a few.   “Following the overwhelming demand from our fans in South Africa, we are excited to return to Cape Town and Johannesburg, and bring WWE LIVE to Pretoria for the first time,” said Stefan Kastenmüller, Senior Vice President & General Manager, WWE Africa, Europe & Emerging Markets. “WWE fans in South Africa can look forward to spectacular, non-stop, family-friendly entertainment featuring their favourite WWE Superstars.”   WWE LIVE SOUTH AFRICA is promoted by Big Concerts and presented in partnership with SuperSport, Africa’s premier sports broadcaster, that airs WWE programming in more than 50 countries and territories throughout sub-Saharan Africa. DM   
